<section class="sec" id="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-h">
  <div class="lc">
    <div class="problem-inner">
      <!-- Left: copy -->
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow rv">The Problem</span>
        <h2 id="problem-h" class="h2 rv" style="transition-delay:0.08s;margin-bottom:2rem">
          Two founders. Same problem.<br>Different disguise.
        </h2>

        <div class="body-lg rv" style="transition-delay:0.16s">
          <p>
            You built something real. The product works, the clients stay, referrals trickle in.
            But outside your existing circle? Silence. You're the best-kept secret in your industry,
            and that's not the compliment it sounds like.
          </p>
          <p>
            Or perhaps you're not invisible at all. You post. You publish. You show up. And yet the
            leads are tepid, the deals take too long, and the people who find you don't understand
            what you actually do. Activity without architecture is just noise with a content calendar.
          </p>
          <p>
            That gap between what you've built and what the market sees? That's not a marketing problem.
            That's a strategic one.
          </p>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="problem-pull rv" style="transition-delay:0.28s">
          You have a reputation, but not a brand. One requires proximity. The other works while you sleep.
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: data as typographic elements -->
      <div class="problem-stats in-view" data-anim-stats>
        <div class="p-stat rv" style="transition-delay:0.1s">
          <span class="p-stat-num">82<span style="font-size:0.55em">%</span></span>
          <p class="p-stat-label">of B2B buyers trust a founder's personal content over corporate marketing</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-stat rv" style="transition-delay:0.2s">
          <span class="p-stat-num">73<span style="font-size:0.55em">%</span></span>
          <p class="p-stat-label">of B2B decisions are influenced by the seller's personal reputation</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-stat rv" style="transition-delay:0.3s">
          <span class="p-stat-num">65<span style="font-size:0.55em">%</span></span>
          <p class="p-stat-label">of executives say thought leadership directly influenced a purchasing decision</p>
        </div>
        <p style="font-family:var(--fB);font-size:0.5625rem;color:var(--t3);margin-top:1.5rem">
          Sources: Edelman Trust Barometer 2024 · LinkedIn B2B Thought Leadership Impact Study
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
